abstract: >-
  A multi-layered evidentiary package arguing that AI has entered a rapid,
  self-reinforcing phase transition that meets the majority of singularity
  criteria. Built across six independent layers of evidence — narrative
  argument, quantitative proof, adversarial analysis, prediction registry,
  historical comparison, and a live falsification engine — and published
  alongside two formal independent adversarial reviews. Includes 65 data
  points across 7 benchmark domains, curve fitting with AIC model selection,
  Fisher's combined probability analysis, 20 timestamped falsifiable
  predictions, and a built environment lifecycle impact analysis covering
  14 stakeholder groups across 7 lifecycle phases.
